<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871124-0155 </DOCNO><HL> Litton Unit ReceivesContract From Navy</HL><DD> 11/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LIT LK UTX GE FIGIAAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ingalls Shipbuilding, a unit of Litton Industries Inc., won a $378.7 million Navy contract for construction of amphibious assault ships.    Lockheed Missiles andamp; Space Co., a unit of Lockheed Corp., was issued a $157.5 million Navy contract for processing and support services for ballistic missiles.    Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., received a $53.9 million Navy contract for production of C-MH53 helicopters.    General Electric Co. was awarded a $29.5 million Army contract for T-700 helicopter engines.    Interstate Electronics Corp., a unit of Figgie International Inc., received a $24.7 million Navy contract for equipment for Trident missile tests. </TEXT></DOC>